parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Inadequate Seat Belt Design and Fit
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt to fit properly can lead to discomfort, difficulty in use, and potentially, failure to provide adequate protection in the event of an accident, increasing the risk of injury or fatality.
symptoms: The seat belt does not fit comfortably
the seat belt is too short
the seat belt does not adjust properly
the driver or passenger is unable to buckle up due to seat belt design or fit issues.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The corrosion of the seat belt anchor can cause it to pull out of the wheel well, leading to a loss of seat belt functionality and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt anchor is loose or detached
the seat belt is no longer securely attached to the vehicle
rust or corrosion is visible on the seat belt anchor or surrounding area.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Defective Seat Belt Buckle or Retractor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt buckle or retractor can prevent the seat belt from functioning properly, increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt buckle is difficult or impossible to fasten
the seat belt buckle will not latch or unlatch
the seat belt retractor locks up or fails to retract
the seat belt requires excessive force or manipulation to buckle or unbuckle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Rusting of exhaust system components can lead to exhaust leaks, which can cause carbon monoxide poisoning, decreased vehicle performance, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Rattling or hissing sounds from the exhaust system
decreased engine performance
decreased fuel efficiency
visible rust or corrosion on exhaust system components.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A faulty idle air control system can cause the engine to stall or idle erratically, leading to loss of vehicle control, especially on cold or icy days.
symptoms: Engine stalling
high or low idle
erratic shifting
loss of power while driving
frequent need to pull over to allow the problem to correct itself.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A cracked PCV vacuum unit housing can cause engine oil leaks, decreased engine performance, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Engine oil leaks
decreased engine performance
increased emissions
visible cracks or damage to the PCV vacuum unit housing.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Valve cover gasket failure can cause engine oil leaks, decreased engine performance, and increased emissions.
symptoms: Engine oil leaks
decreased engine performance
increased emissions
visible signs of oil leakage around the valve cover.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective timing belt can cause engine damage, decreased engine performance, and potentially lead to engine failure.
symptoms: Engine failure
decreased engine performance
visible signs of timing belt damage or breakage.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Rusted Gas Filler Neck and Contaminated Fuel Line
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A rusted gas filler neck and contaminated fuel line can cause fuel leaks, stalling, and rough idling, which can lead to accidents, fires, and leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
stalling
rough idling
car won't start
fuel leaking out of the carburetor
water leaks into the trunk where the fuel filler pipe mounts to the wheel well and trunk area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Frame corrosion or rust can lead to structural weakening, compromising the vehicle's integrity and potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Rust or corrosion on the frame
particularly in areas such as the front crossmember bar or rear left side of the frame
can cause the frame to weaken or break
leading to loss of vehicle control or collapse.
